{"cells":[{"cell_type":"code","source":["from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"AB4jj--rcg9P","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781194250744,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1450,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"f96f0785-53da-4f70-ca5b-26acef6553dd"},"execution_count":2,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Drive already mounted at /content/drive; to attempt to forcibly remount, call drive.mount(\"/content/drive\", force_remount=True).\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%cd /content/drive/MyDrive/Repos/datasets"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"h56rnvrocjTG","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781194252443,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"c816675f-3f30-469d-e34f-96675e84b9f6"},"execution_count":3,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["/content/drive/MyDrive/Repos/datasets\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **1. Introduction to Topic Modeling and LDA**\n","\n","**Topic modeling** is an unsupervised learning task that assigns topic categories to unlabeled text documents (e.g., clustering newspaper articles into sports, finance, politics, etc.).\n","\n","**Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA)** is a popular generative probabilistic model used for this task. It takes a bag-of-words matrix as input and decomposes it into two new matrices:\n","\n","1. A document-to-topic matrix\n","2. A word-to-topic matrix\n","\n","When multiplied together, these matrices reproduce the original bag-of-words matrix with the lowest possible error. The primary hyperparameter you must define manually is the number of topics.\n","\n","---\n","\n","### **2. Data Preparation and Vectorization**\n","\n","To apply LDA, we first read the dataset and use `CountVectorizer` to create a bag-of-words matrix.\n","\n","* **`max_df=.1`**: Excludes words occurring in more than 10% of documents (removes common words less likely to be topic-specific).\n","* **`max_features=5000`**: Limits the vocabulary to the 5,000 most frequent words to improve inference and manage dimensionality."],"metadata":{"id":"6yNGzPuWb7_G"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer\n","\n","# Load dataset\n","df = pd.read_csv('movie_data.csv', encoding='utf-8')\n","# Rename columns if necessary (depends on your CSV header)\n","df = df.rename(columns={\"0\": \"review\", \"1\": \"sentiment\"})\n","\n","# Initialize CountVectorizer\n","count = CountVectorizer(stop_words='english',\n","                        max_df=.1,\n","                        max_features=5000)\n","\n","# Create the bag-of-words matrix\n","X = count.fit_transform(df['review'].values)"],"outputs":[],"execution_count":4,"metadata":{"id":"stN6hykVb7_I","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781194263962,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":10713,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","### **3. Fitting the LDA Model**\n","\n","Next, we use scikit-learn's `LatentDirichletAllocation` class to categorize the dataset into 10 different topics.\n","\n","* **`learning_method='batch'`**: Updates estimates based on all available training data in one iteration (slower but potentially more accurate). Alternatively, `'online'` acts like mini-batch learning.\n","* *(Note: Model fitting may take up to 5 minutes on a standard machine).*"],"metadata":{"id":"Nnp6CX-Kb7_K"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.decomposition import LatentDirichletAllocation\n","\n","# Initialize LDA for 10 topics\n","lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=10,\n","                                random_state=123,\n","                                learning_method='batch')\n","\n","# Fit and transform the data\n","X_topics = lda.fit_transform(X)"],"outputs":[],"execution_count":5,"metadata":{"id":"l3uqBHlUb7_K","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781194639886,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":370415,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","### **4. Analyzing the Extracted Topics**\n","\n","After fitting the model, the `components_` attribute stores a matrix containing the word importance for each of the 10 topics. We can sort this array to find the top 5 most important words that characterize each topic."],"metadata":{"id":"8u7akHJkb7_L"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["n_top_words = 5\n","feature_names = count.get_feature_names_out()\n","\n","for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):\n","    print(f'Topic {(topic_idx + 1)}:')\n","    # Sort the topic array in reverse order to get the most important words\n","    print(' '.join([feature_names[i]\n","                    for i in topic.argsort()[:-n_top_words - 1:-1]]))"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Topic 1:\n","horror worst script effects budget\n","Topic 2:\n","dvd watched video music guy\n","Topic 3:\n","war american series history documentary\n","Topic 4:\n","game killer murder thriller crime\n","Topic 5:\n","kids comedy episode series school\n","Topic 6:\n","family woman mother beautiful feel\n","Topic 7:\n","role performance comedy john plays\n","Topic 8:\n","action horror john effects dr\n","Topic 9:\n","book version original read music\n","Topic 10:\n","action wife father police james\n"]}],"execution_count":6,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"XGejrjHWb7_L","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781194639904,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":14,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"d85f1de7-63c7-4477-8583-e3b534b48c03"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **5. Confirming Categories with Data Samples**\n","\n","To verify that the model successfully clustered the documents, we can isolate a specific topic (e.g., Topic 3 / index 2: Documentaries) and print the first 300 characters of the top matching reviews in that category."],"metadata":{"id":"j7B8GJRNb7_M"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Sort the documents by their association with Topic 3 (index 2)\n","horror = X_topics[:, 2].argsort()[::-1]\n","\n","# Print the first 300 characters of the top 3 movies in this topic\n","for iter_idx, movie_idx in enumerate(horror[:3]):\n","    print(f'\\nComedy movie #{(iter_idx + 1)}:')\n","    print(df['review'][movie_idx][:300], '...')"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Comedy movie #1:\n","The Drug Years actually suffers from one of those aspects to mini-series or other kinds of TV documentaries run over and over again for a couple of weeks on TV. It's actually not long enough, in a way. All of the major bases in the decades are covered, and they're all interesting to note as views in ...\n","\n","Comedy movie #2:\n","Not a balanced point of view. The director shouldn't express her opinion as truth. The movie has some criticism of Fujimori but it always gives him and his family the last words. So few critics of Fujimori were provided that it seems the only reason they were included was to be able to say the movie ...\n","\n","Comedy movie #3:\n","This series, produced at probably the most propitious time following the events of the second World War, is on a scale of value that stands far above any individual's presumption to criticize.<br /><br />The timing of World at War's production in 1974, amounting to some three decades after the event ...\n"]}],"execution_count":10,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Ryc-_xAFb7_M","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781194972031,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":13,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"f4df94a4-ac43-467a-841a-d75897664e14"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["*The resulting output will print reviews that distinctly sound like they are discussing documentary films (e.g., Second World War), confirming the unsupervised model correctly identified the genre.*"],"metadata":{"id":"Z-NiQZfwb7_M"}}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}